# Poller resilience contract

The poller is a long-running process. A transient upstream failure or one bad
city must never stop collection. Follow these rules exactly.

## Fetching (`app/weather_client.py`)
- Retry a failed fetch up to `settings.max_retries` times with **linear backoff**
  (`backoff_seconds * attempt`).
- Log **every failed attempt at WARNING** with, at minimum: `city`,
  `http_status` (when an HTTP status exists), `attempt`, and `max_retries`.
  Use the `extra=` kwarg — never f-string these values into the message.
- After retries are exhausted, raise `WeatherAPIError(city, message, status, attempts)`.
  Do not return partial or `None` readings.

## Polling loop (`app/poller.py`)
- The network fetch (`client.fetch_current`) MUST happen **outside** any
  `session_scope()` block. Never hold a DB transaction open across network I/O.
- `run_cycle` MUST contain per-city failures: catch `WeatherAPIError`
  (log WARNING with `city`, `http_status`, `attempts`, then continue) and catch
  any other `Exception` (`logger.exception(...)`, then continue). One city
  failing never aborts the others or the loop.
- Only run detection and store events when `store_reading` returns
  `created is True`. A duplicate reading produces no events.
- Honour `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT`: set the `_stop` flag and use `_interruptible_sleep`
  so the container shuts down promptly and cleanly.
